      Subclasses of AbstractAttribute in com.googlecode.cqengine.attribute 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      class  MultiValueAttribute<O,A>
      Represents an attribute in an object which has multiple values (such as a field which is itself a collection), where all of the values are known to be non-null.
      class  MultiValueNullableAttribute<O,A>
      Represents an attribute in an object which has multiple values (such as a field which is itself a collection), where some of the values might be null, or where the collection of values itself might be null.
      class  OrderControlAttribute<O>
      An attribute which wraps another delegate attribute, and can be used in a QueryFactory.orderBy(AttributeOrder) clause to control the placement in results of objects which have and do not have values for the delegate attribute.
      class  OrderMissingFirstAttribute<O>
      An OrderControlAttribute which orders results such that objects without values for the given delegate attribute are always returned before objects with values for the attribute.
      class  OrderMissingLastAttribute<O>
      An OrderControlAttribute which orders results such that objects without values for the given delegate attribute are always returned after objects with values for the attribute.
      class  ReflectiveAttribute<O,A>
      A type of SimpleAttribute which is implemented using reflection.
      class  SelfAttribute<O>
      An attribute which returns the object itself.
      class  SimpleAttribute<O,A>
      Represents an attribute in an object (such as a field) which will not be null.
      class  SimpleNullableAttribute<O,A>
      Represents an attribute in an object (such as a field) which can be null.
      class  SimpleNullableMapAttribute<K,A>
      An attribute which reads the value from an entry in a map given the map key.
      class  StandingQueryAttribute<O>
      An attribute which wraps a query or query fragment.
